- `/apps/v4/registry/bases/base/examples/_registry.ts` - Example/demo definitions
- `/apps/v4/registry/bases/base/components/_registry.ts` - Complex components
- `/apps/v4/registry/bases/base/hooks/_registry.ts` - Custom hooks
- `/apps/v4/registry/bases/base/lib/_registry.ts` - Utility libraries
- `/apps/v4/registry/bases/base/blocks/_registry.ts` - Multi-file blocks

**Schema Definitions:**
- `/packages/shadcn/src/registry/schema.ts` - TypeScript Zod schema (source of truth)
- `/apps/v4/public/schema/registry-item.json` - JSON schema (must match TypeScript schema)

**Generated/Runtime Files:**
- `/apps/v4/registry/bases/__index__.tsx` - Auto-generated index with lazy-loaded components
- `/apps/v4/registry/__index__.tsx` - Combined index across all styles

---

### Registry Item Types

The registry supports these types (from `registryItemTypeSchema`):

1. **`registry:ui`** - Single-file UI components/primitives
2. **`registry:block`** - Complex multi-file components
3. **`registry:component`** - Simple components
4. **`registry:hook`** - Custom React hooks
5. **`registry:lib`** - Utility functions and helpers
6. **`registry:page`** - Page or route files (requires `target`)
7. **`registry:file`** - Miscellaneous files (requires `target`)
8. **`registry:theme`** - Theme configuration
9. **`registry:style`** - Style/design system definitions
10. **`registry:base`** - Entire design system bases
11. **`registry:font`** - Font definitions (requires `font` metadata)
12. **`registry:example`** - Demo/example components (internal)

---

### Schema for Registering a New UI Component

**Minimal UI Component Registration** (`registry:ui` type):

```typescript
{
  name: "accordion",
  type: "registry:ui",
  files: [
    {
      path: "ui/accordion.tsx",
      type: "registry:ui",
    },
  ],
  meta: {
    links: {
      docs: "https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components/base/accordion",
      examples: "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/...",
      api: "https://base-ui.com/react/components/accordion.md",
    },
  },
}
```

**Full UI Component with Dependencies**:

```typescript
{
  name: "carousel",
  type: "registry:ui",
  description: "A carousel component with embla-carousel",
  files: [
    {
      path: "ui/carousel.tsx",
      type: "registry:ui",
    },
  ],
  registryDependencies: ["button"],           // Other shadcn/ui components
  dependencies: ["embla-carousel-react"],     // npm packages
  devDependencies: ["tw-animate-css"],        // Dev-only npm packages
  meta: {
    links: {
      docs: "https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components/base/carousel",
      examples: "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/...",
      api: "https://www.embla-carousel.com/get-started/react",
    },
  },
}
```

**Compound Component with Multiple Sub-Exports** (single file):

Even compound components like `Accordion`, `Tabs`, `DropdownMenu` are registered as a **single file** (`registry:ui`), despite exporting multiple sub-components:

```typescript
// ui/accordion.tsx exports:
export function Accordion({ ... })
export function AccordionItem({ ... })
export function AccordionTrigger({ ... })
export function AccordionContent({ ... })

// But registered as:
{
  name: "accordion",
  type: "registry:ui",
  files: [
    {
      path: "ui/accordion.tsx",
      type: "registry:ui",
    },
  ],
  // ...
}
```

The key insight: **A single registry entry can export multiple named exports from one file**.

---

### Schema for Registering an Example/Demo

**Example Entry Format** (uses `registry:example` type):

```typescript
{
  name: "accordion-example",
  title: "Accordion",                    // Human-readable title
  type: "registry:example",
  registryDependencies: [
    "accordion",                          // Components the example uses
    "button",
    "card",
    "example",                            // Base example wrapper component
  ],
  files: [
    {
      path: "examples/accordion-example.tsx",
      type: "registry:example",
    },
  ],
}
```

**Example File Structure** (`accordion-example.tsx`):

```typescript
import {
